  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study addresses epidemiology of cardiovascular risk factors and major cardiovascular
      diseases in Russian Federation (urban and rural population). 12 regions of 1600 participants
      in each will be included.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Plasma lipids and fasting glucose, heart rate and blood pressure, anthropometry, smoking and
      alcohol questionaries, nutrition, sleep quality, stress will be assessed. ECG records are
      obtained form all participants. Subclinical target organ damage (carotid and periferal
      atherosclerosis, pulse wave velocity) will be measured in selected sites. Brain natriuretic
      peptide, adipose tissue cytokines, hsCRP and genetic markers are also under evaluation
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
